12/01/2004
TEHRAN, Iran -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul met on Saturday (10 January) with President Muhammad Khatami during an official visit to Iran. They discussed bilateral relations and co-operation in the fight against terrorism. Khatami condemned the November terrorist attacks in Istanbul and commended Turkish authorities for their resolute struggle against terrorism. He pledged that no terrorist organisation or enemy of Turkey would be allowed to use Iranian territory to launch attacks against Turkey. (Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 10/01/04)
